otball/former-dupont-star-athlete-minnesota-viking-eric-moss-dies-at/article_7d5a7558-8534-592b-8f0e-b0f14ec770cd.html Former DuPont star athlete, Minnesota Viking Eric Moss dies at 44]</ref>\n* [[March 21]] - [[Anthony Dickerson]], player (b. [[1957]])<ref>[https://247sports.com/nfl/dallas-cowboys/Article/Anthony-Dickerson-passes-away-Dallas-Cowboys--130556744/ Former Cowboys linebacker Anthony Dickerson passes away]</ref>\n* [[March 23]] - [[Clem Daniels]], player (b. [[1937]])<ref>[https://www.sfchronicle.com/raiders/article/Clem-Daniels-one-of-Raiders-all-time-best-13715331.php Clem Daniels, one of Raiders\u2019 all-time best RBs, has died]</ref>\n* [[March 27]] \u2013 [[Joe Bellino]], player (b. [[1938]])<ref>[https://www.boston25news.com/sports/joe-bellino-1960-heisman-winner-and-winchester-native-passes-away-at-81/935182195 Joe Bellino, 1960 Heisman winner and Winchester native, dies at 81]</ref>\n* [[April 8]] - [[Blase Bonpane]], player (b. [[1929]])<ref>[https://www.latimes.com/local/california/la-me-blase-bonpane-dead-20190410-story.html Blase Bonpane, USC football player turned priest turned peace activist, dies at 89]</ref>\n* [[April 17]] - [[Chet Coppock]], broadcast journalist and [[sports talk]] personality (b. [[1948]])<ref>[https://abc7chicago.com/sports/chet-coppock-dies-at-70/5257745/ Chet Coppock, Chicago sports broadcaster, dies at 70 after car accident]</ref>\n* [[April 20]] - [[Reggie Cobb]], player (b. [[1968]])<ref>[https://www.sacbee.com/sports/nfl/san-francisco-49ers/article229506819.html 49ers scout Reggie Cobb dies from suspected heart attack]</ref>\n* [[April 24]] - [[Johnny Green (gridiron football)|Johnny Green]], player (b. [[1937]])<ref>[https://www.chattanoogan.com/2019/4/25/389105/John-Johnny-Edward-Green.aspx John \"Johnny\" Edward Green]</ref>\n* [[April 29]] - [[Gino Marchetti]], player (b. [[1925]])<ref>[http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/26639921/hall-fame-de-gino-marchetti-dies-92 Hall of Fame DE Gino Marchetti dies at 92]